This paper deals with combinatorial auctions, which are a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.DS). The online primal dual framework is a popular technique in online algorithms (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses incentive compatibility, which is a key concept in mechanism design (cs.EC).
